The executive director shall implement and oversee the licensure process of advanced imaging professionals, medical imaging technologists, radiographers, radiation therapists, nuclear medicine technologists, and limited X-ray machine operators as defined by the board. The executive director shall, at a minimum:
Receive and evaluate applications for licenses;
Document continuing education by licensees;
Report suspected allegations of violations of this chapter to the board;
Serve as corresponding secretary for the board;
Supervise and evaluate administrative assistants and other office staff hired or contracted by the board;
Assist the board chair in coordinating regular and special meetings and agendas;
Maintain records of the actions of the board;
Obtain an annual audit of the funds received and disbursed;
Prepare and submit reports as needed;
Serve as liaison between educational programs and the board; and
Serve as liaison between the board and:
State and national professional and accrediting organizations; and
Other Kentucky boards and agencies.
